BTC tracker dashboard.

Live app:
- https://mjamiv.github.io/btc_tracker/

Local run:
- Open `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/index.html` in a browser.
- Use **Add Transaction** to store new entries locally in your browser.
- Use **Export Updated CSV** to download a merged `transactions.csv` that includes local additions.

Automations:
- Daily historical BTC prices are refreshed by `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/.github/workflows/update-historical-prices.yml`.
- Security scans run in `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/.github/workflows/security-sweep.yml`.
- Coinbase fills can be synced to `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/transactions.csv` by `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/.github/workflows/sync-coinbase-transactions.yml`.

Security note:
- GitHub Pages is public-by-design for static assets. See `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/SECURITY.md` before redeploying sensitive data.

Coinbase sync setup:
- Add repo secret `COINBASE_API_KEY` (Advanced Trade API key name).
- Add repo secret `COINBASE_API_SECRET` (Advanced Trade API private key PEM).
- Trigger `Sync Coinbase Transactions` workflow or wait for the 15-minute schedule.
- Sync logic lives in `/Users/mjamiv/coding/btc-chart/btc_tracker/scripts/sync_coinbase_transactions.py`.
